[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/The art room feels different now—quieter heavier..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
The art room feels different now. Quieter. Heavy with the weight of what happened.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (animated) leftmost
	join Mark (Mark_half) left
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Conrad and Mark stand near the doorway watching in silence..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Celestine and Mark stand near the door, watching the scene unfold.
else:
	join Conrad (half) leftmost
	join Mark (Mark_half) left
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Conrad and Mark stand near the doorway watching in silence..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Conrad and Mark stand near the door, watching the scene unfold.
join "Ms Reyes" (half) center
Ms. Reyes stands near her desk, her expression a mix of disappointment and sadness.
join Victor (half) right
Victor sits on a stool, shoulders hunched, unable to meet anyone's eyes.
"Ms Reyes": Victor. I've always believed in your talent.
"Ms Reyes": But talent without empathy is just... technique. Empty movements.
Victor: I know. I understand that now.
"Ms Reyes": The principal has decided on your consequences.
"Ms Reyes": You'll be suspended from the art program for the rest of the semester.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Victor winces but does not argue..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Victor winces but doesn't protest.
"Ms Reyes": And you'll help organize next year's Art Week. Setting up displays. Supporting other students.
"Ms Reyes": Learning that art is about community, not competition.
Victor nods slowly.
Victor: That's... that's fair. More than fair.
leave Victor
leave "Ms Reyes"
[wait time="0.5"]
join Mia (half) right
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia enters quietly. Her eyes are red but her expression is steady..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Mia enters quietly. Her eyes are still red, but her expression is steady.
Victor looks up as she approaches. He flinches, expecting anger.
join Victor (half) center
Victor: Mia... I...
Mia: Let me speak first.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Victor falls silent bracing himself..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Victor falls silent.
Mia: Victor, I always thought you were amazing.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Victor looks up surprised..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Victor looks up, genuinely surprised.
Mia: Your technical skill is incredible. The way you render light and shadow...
Mia: I could never do what you do. I just... feel things and try to capture them.
Mia: We're different kinds of artists. Neither is better.
Victor: But everyone loves your work. No one even looks at mine.
Mia: Because you make it hard to connect with you.
Mia: Your art is perfect, but it feels... closed. Like you're trying to prove something.
Mia: Art isn't about proving. It's about sharing.
Victor: I... I never thought of it that way.
Mia: My sculpture wasn't meant to win competitions.
Mia: I made it because I missed my grandfather. I wanted to remember how it felt when he read to me.
Mia: The judges responded to that feeling. Not the technique.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Victor's voice breaks..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Victor's voice breaks.
Victor: And I destroyed it because I was jealous.
Victor: I'm so sorry, Mia. I'm so, so sorry.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia takes a slow breath..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
Mia takes a deep breath, steadying herself.
Mia: I can't forgive you yet. It hurts too much.
Mia: But... I understand hurt. I understand feeling invisible.
Mia: Destroying my art didn't make yours better. It just destroyed something beautiful.
Mia: I hope you learn from this. I really do.
Victor: I will. I promise I will.
Victor: And someday... someday I'll create something that honors what I destroyed.
Victor: Something with heart. Something real.
Mia nods slowly.
Mia: I'd like to see that.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia turns toward the door and pauses beside Conrad..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Mia turns and walks toward the door, pausing beside Celestine.
	Mia: Thank you. For finding the truth.
	Celestine: The truth was always there. I just helped it come to light.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia leaves the room..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Mia manages a small, sad smile before leaving.
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia turns toward the door and pauses beside Conrad..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Mia turns and walks toward the door, pausing beside Conrad.
	Mia: Thank you. For finding the truth.
	Conrad: The truth was always there. I just helped it come to light.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Mia leaves the room..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Mia manages a small, sad smile before leaving.
leave Mia
leave Victor
[background arg="res://Bg/art_room.png" fade="0.5"]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Conrad and Mark remain surrounded by unfinished art and heavy thoughts..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Celestine and Mark remain in the art room.
	Mark: That was... heavy.
	Celestine: Justice isn't always satisfying.
	Celestine: Victor will face consequences. But the real punishment is what he's feeling right now.
	Mark: Mia was surprisingly kind. I don't know if I could have been.
	Celestine: She's an artist. She understands that pain can make people do terrible things.
	Celestine: That doesn't excuse what Victor did. But understanding matters.
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s5/Conrad and Mark remain surrounded by unfinished art and heavy thoughts..mp3" volume=0 bus="Master"]
	Conrad and Mark remain in the art room.
